content.value: kernel supports outputting most primitive node types. The
function is patched so that each argument is a separate output:

content.code:
print(TRUE)
print(1)
print(2.34)
print("string")
print(c(1, 2, 3))
print(list(a=1, b=2))

content.value: There is also support for outputting of data frames:

content.code:
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=cyl, y=mpg, color=carb)) + geom_point()
